{"id":"hep-ph/0202072","submitter":"Barbot Cyrille","authors":"Cyrille Barbot and Manuel Drees","title":"Production of ultra-energetic cosmic rays through the decay of\n  super-heavy X particles","comments":"13 pages, 6 figures. Minor corrections and new references. To be\n  published in Physics Letters B","journal-ref":"Phys.Lett.B533:107-115,2002","doi":"10.1016/S0370-2693(02)01621-0","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-ph astro-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We present a new and complete numerical analysis of the decay of super-heavy\nX particles, assumed to be the origin of cosmic rays with energy beyond the GZK\ncut-off. The decay of X initiates a ``parton shower'', where we include all\ndegrees of freedom contained in the Minimal Supersymmetric Standard Model\n(MSSM). Since at energies near $M_X$ all gauge couplings are of similar\nmagnitude, we include all of them, as well as third generation Yukawa\ncouplings. Technically the shower development is described through the DGLAP\nevolution of the relevant fragmentation functions (FFs). We also carefully\ntreat the decay of the superparticles as well as heavy SM particles created in\nthe shower. Nonperturbative physics is parameterized through the input values\nof the FFs, which we take from the literature. The final result is the the\ncomplete spectrum of all stable particles at the very end of the shower :\nprotons, electrons, neutrinos, photons and neutralinos, for an energy range\nfrom $10^{-7} M_X$ to $M_X$. In particular, the flux of high-energy neutralinos\nis sizable ; it might serve as ``smoking gun'' signature for this kind of\nscenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Feb 2002 18:23:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 Apr 2002 09:32:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-17"}
{"id":"hep-ph/0202073","submitter":"Jacques C. R. Bloch","authors":"J.C.R. Bloch","title":"Multiplicative renormalizability and quark propagator","comments":"17 pages; minor corrections, comparison to lattice results added;\n  accepted for publication in Phys. Rev. D","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev.D66:034032,2002","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.66.034032","report-no":"UNITU-THEP-02/02","categories":"hep-ph hep-lat hep-th nucl-th","license":null,"abstract":"  The renormalized Dyson-Schwinger equation for the quark propagator is\nstudied, in Landau gauge, in a novel truncation which preserves multiplicative\nrenormalizability. The renormalization constants are formally eliminated from\nthe integral equations, and the running coupling explicitly enters the kernels\nof the new equations. To construct a truncation which preserves multiplicative\nrenormalizability, and reproduces the correct leading order perturbative\nbehavior, non-trivial cancellations involving the full quark-gluon vertex are\nassumed in the quark self-energy loop. A model for the running coupling is\nintroduced, with infrared fixed point in agreement with previous\nDyson-Schwinger studies of the gauge sector, and with correct logarithmic tail.\nDynamical chiral symmetry breaking is investigated, and the generated quark\nmass is of the order of the extension of the infrared plateau of the coupling,\nand about three times larger than in the Abelian approximation, which violates\nmultiplicative renormalizability. The generated scale is of the right size for\nhadronic phenomenology, without requiring an infrared enhancement of the\nrunning coupling.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Feb 2002 19:10:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 Jul 2002 14:39:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-01-14"}
